The style linter complains: you should put the module docstring before any open statements.

How about this?
The `check_declID` linter emits a warning on declarations whose name is non-standard style.
(Currently, this only includes declarations whose names include a double underscore.)
This is not an identifier *name* (but syntax corresponding to one), right? Can you tweak the comment to make this clearer?
I like these lines! Can you move this above the the `register_option`, then you can just use `@[inherit_doc] here.
Subjective: I would put the `run` on the the same line. I would also name the variable `stx`, and find a different name below. Both of these are matters of taste.
I think mathlib style is to not brace if conditions.
You can omit these two lines, right?

pullRequest.title: chore(Tactic/Linter/Style): check declIDs
